title: Eduardo Duhalde
summary: Eduardo Alberto Duhalde (Spanish pronunciation: [eˈðwaɾdo alˈβeɾto ˈðwalde]; born 5 October 1941)[1] is an Argentine Peronist politician who served as the interim President of Argentina from January 2002 to May 2003.[2] He also served as Vice President and Governor of Buenos Aires in the 1990s.
